news.title: Haryana CM counsels slum dwellers to get rehabilitated
news.para: The CM was interacting with the mediapersons soon after inspecting the land identified for rehabilitation at Kharak Mangoli village. Haryana Vidhan Sabha speaker Gian Chand Gupta was also present along the CM.

news.title: Ludhiana to get 1,000 street lights using advanced technology
news.para: Lights will be installed in selected areas under the Smart City Mission. These include BRS Nagar road, Hambran road, College Road, DMC road, Pakhowal road, Ghumar Mandi, OLD GT road, main Rahon road, Malhar Road to Hero Bakery chowk etc...

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM to distribute house sites to poor in Ongole
news.para: Along with social welfare minister Dr Merugu Nagarjuna, municipal administration minister Dr Adimulapu Suresh, and district collector AS Dinesh Kumar, Balineni Srinivas Reddy inspected the arrangements at Agraharam village on the outskirts of Ongole city.

news.title: Building rules across Tamil Nadu being rewired
news.para: For a review of the 2019-enacted Tamil Nadu Combined Development and Building Rules (TNCDBR), Chennai Metropolitan Development Authority (CMDA) roped in Ahmedabad-based CEPT Research and Development Foundation Ahmedabad that completed it after stakeholder meetings across TN.

news.title: Yogi Construction Company buys residential plot for Rs 450 crore in Gift City
news.para: According to sources, this will be the biggest residential project so far in the Gift City. The plot is situated in the domestic zone of the Gift City and the bids were invited for around 11.60 lakh sq feet development rights.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates may get back land if it clears Rs 200 crore dues
news.para: About 1,000 hectares were allotted to Jaypee International Sports, a subsidiary of JAL, in 2009-10 under a special development zone (SDZ) scheme in Sector 25 for developing a Sports City.

news.title: Supreme Constructions' MD who 'duped' flat purchasers moves HC to quash FIRs
news.para: A builder has approached the Bombay high court seeking clubbing and quashing FIRs against him for allegedly duping flat purchasers in a housing project in Taloja, Navi Mumbai. T

news.title: Gurugram: Builders yet to pay for structural audit, may lose registration
news.para: In a recent meeting attended by ADC Hitesh Kumar Meena and district town planner (enforcement) Manish Yadav, the DTP issued instructions to stop registration of projects of builders who do not cooperate in structural audit work.

news.title: Karnataka Assembly passes bill slashing penalty on property tax in Bengaluru by 50%
news.para: ​​Deputy Chief Minister D K Shivakumar, who holds the Bengaluru development portfolio, tabled the bill in the Legislative Assembly.​​"With the passing of this Amendment Bill, the penalty amount is halved, saving Bengalureans a whopping Rs 2,700 crores.

news.title: Delhi HC directs DDA and MCD to put structural reforms in place
news.para: The issue of overlapping jurisdiction needs to be resolved by issuing clear and cogent practice directions," a bench of Acting Chief Justice Manmohan and Justice Manmeet P S Arora said.

news.title: Vibhor Steel Tubes surges 193% in debut trade
news.para: The stock made its debut at Rs 421, reflecting gains of 178.81 per cent from the issue price on the BSE. The stock settled at Rs 442, up by 192.72 per cent over the IPO price.

news.title: Sweden's Oscar Properties says CEO and CFO resign
news.para: Oscar Properties, one of several highly indebted Swedish real estate groups buckling under soaring borrowing costs and slower demand, said in a statement Carl Janglin would stay on as CEO until a successor had been appointed.

news.title: Delhi: Signature View Apartments RWA asks DDA for payment of rent to residents willing to evacuate
news.para: ​According to the letter dated February 15, it has been almost 15 months since the IIT-Delhi report recommended immediate evacuation and dismantling of the towers in the housing society to save lives of allottees/residents.

news.title: Germany: Adler Group's chairman resigns
news.para: Following an extraordinary meeting of the board of directors, the major German landlord said Stefan Brendgen would replace Kirsten with immediate effect.

news.title: China cuts mortgage reference rate more than expected to revive property market
news.para: The five-year loan prime rate (LPR) was lowered by 25 basis points to 3.95% from 4.20% previously, while the one-year LPR was left unchanged at 3.45%.

news.title: Greater Noida: Industrial plot allotment scheme extended till February 27
news.para: The Industrial Scheme was floated by the Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) with a registration closing date of February 19.

news.title: Jaipur: JDA to utilise land pooling act to acquire 164 hectares for Shivdaspura township
news.para: JDA officials stated that although the Act was framed in 2016, neither the earlier BJP government nor the previous Congress government used this Act.

news.title: Goa: Stone crushing units told to install CCTVs, no ops without GSPCB nod
news.para: Any new crushers should be allowed to operate only in dedicated crusher zones according to the sitting policies of GSPCB, the guidelines state.

news.title: Gujarat government to install 10 lakh solar panels under PM scheme
news.para: Solar Rooftop Scheme Surya-Gujarat Scheme was launched by the state govt from Aug 5, 2019, for the purpose of providing relief in electricity bills to residential consumers in the state and boost green energy generation.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body to auction bulk land parcels, vacant plots
news.para: These VMRDA auctions will not only gauge the current market sentiment but also potentially influence real estate prices in neighbouring areas.
